SIMPLE: mucoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mucoid
<hw>Mu"coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mucus</ets> +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <def>Resembling mucus.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mucoid degeneration</b></col>, <cd>a form of degeneration
in which the tissues are transformed into a semisolid substance
resembling mucus.</cd> <rj><au>Quain.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mucoid
<hw>Mu"coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Muc</ets>in +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a class
of mucinlike substances yielding on decomposition a reducing
carbohydrate together with some form of proteinaceous matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muconate</ent>⟦br⟧
